==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Grapnel
<hw>Grap"nel</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>grapenel</ets>, dim. fr. F. <ets>grappin t</ets>he grapple of a
ship; of German origin. See <er>Grape</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>
<def>A small anchor, with four or five flukes or claws, used to hold
boats or small vessels; hence, any instrument designed to grapple or
hold; a grappling iron; a grab; -- written also <xex>grapline</xex>, and
<xex>crapnel</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Grapple</ent>⟦br⟧
